    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>249</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>104300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#pernierTacc"/> 1930, p. <citedRange>128</citedRange>.</bibl></p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name><gap reason="lost" quantity="7" precision="low" unit="character"/></name> 
                                <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65764"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Τελέσανδρος"><supplied reason="lost">Τ</supplied><unclear>ε</unclear>λεσάνδρω</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλωνι</supplied></name></persName> 
                    <w lemma="δεκάτα"><supplied reason="lost">δ</supplied>εκάταν</w>	 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied> fils de Télésandros <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied>
            à Apollon au titre de la dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> son of Telesandros <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied>
            to Apollo as a tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> figlio di Telesandros <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied>
            ad Apollo come decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Several men named Telesandros are mentioned in inscriptions of the fourth and the third century. As we have here only the father's name, 
                no prosopographical relation may be proposed.</p>
	<p>The exact findspot, not mentioned in our first edition (2017), is provided here thanks to a communication by Enzo Catani from Pernier's notebooks.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
